  <chapter id="rasmol">
    <title>Rasmol Scripts</title>
    <para>
      The scripting language within Jmol is inherited from another
      3D viewer, Rasmol. Note that it this time, only a limited
      amount of commands can be used. All commands mentioned
      in this chapter do.
    </para>
    <section>
      <title>General Commands</title>
      <section>
        <title>load</title>
        <para>
	  <cmdsynopsis>
	    <command>load</command>
	    <arg>format</arg>
            <arg choice="req"><replaceable>filename</replaceable></arg>
	  </cmdsynopsis>
	</para>
        <para>
          Currently accepted formats are PDB, CML and XYZ.
        </para>
      </section>
      <section>
        <title>script</title>
        <para>
	  <cmdsynopsis>
	    <command>script</command>
            <arg choice="req"><replaceable>filename</replaceable></arg>
	  </cmdsynopsis>
	</para>
        <para>
          Loads and execute a script file from disk.
        </para>
      </section>
      <section>
        <title>exit</title>
        <para>
	  <cmdsynopsis>
	    <command>exit</command>
	  </cmdsynopsis>
	</para>
        <para>
          If given from script window, closes this window.
        </para>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Display Commands</title>
      <para> </para>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Colour Commands</title>
      <section>
        <title>colour or color</title>
        <para>
	  <cmdsynopsis>
	    <command>colour</command>
            <arg><replaceable>object</replaceable></arg>
            <arg choice="req"><replaceable>colour</replaceable></arg>
	  </cmdsynopsis>
	</para>
        <para>
	  Gives selected objects a colour as specified by the colour 
          value. Note that color is synonymous with colour.
	</para>
	<para>
	  Currently accepted colour values: black, red, grey, blue, 
          green, cyan, magenta, orange, white and pink.
	</para>
      </section>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>Manipulation Commands</title>
